[{"thread":{"id":"1387620561936715796","type":11,"last_message_id":"1387687596158746635","flags":0,"guild_id":"1212332642801025064","name":"Backup in Infrahub Community","parent_id":"1301914405176475729","rate_limit_per_user":0,"bitrate":64000,"user_limit":0,"rtc_region":null,"owner_id":"720103795090260008","thread_metadata":{"archived":true,"archive_timestamp":"2025-07-26T06:57:26.643000+00:00","auto_archive_duration":4320,"locked":false,"create_timestamp":"2025-06-26T02:28:42.709000+00:00"},"message_count":2,"member_count":2,"total_message_sent":2,"applied_tags":["1322475882421555200","1301916056205656276"]},"messages":[{"type":0,"content":"Thanks üôÇ <@1133022375051542558>","mentions":[{"id":"1133022375051542558","username":"shabear_dis","avatar":"e5046d674427373d76e2dde9dc74feb5","discriminator":"0","public_flags":0,"flags":0,"banner":null,"accent_color":null,"global_name":"Benito","avatar_decoration_data":null,"collectibles":null,"display_name_styles":null,"banner_color":null,"clan":null,"primary_guild":null}],"mention_roles":[],"attachments":[],"embeds":[],"timestamp":"2025-06-26T06:55:04.913000+00:00","edited_timestamp":null,"flags":0,"components":[],"id":"1387687596158746635","channel_id":"1387620561936715796","author":{"id":"720103795090260008","username":"user38128","avatar":null,"discriminator":"0","public_flags":0,"flags":0,"banner":null,"accent_color":null,"global_name":"kuser","avatar_decoration_data":null,"collectibles":null,"display_name_styles":null,"banner_color":null,"clan":null,"primary_guild":null},"pinned":false,"mention_everyone":false,"tts":false,"position":1},{"type":0,"content":"Hello <@720103795090260008> üëã \n\nAt the moment our backup tool is handling only the enterprise version of Neo4j. It is possible to backup a Neo4j Community database, but it need to be done offline.\n\nThe process would be :\n\nYou stop the database docker container, so it‚Äôs:\n```\ndocker stop infrahub-database-1\n```\nYou can list all your Docker volumes with:\n```\ndocker volume ls\n```\nif you have name of volume replace this line\n```\n--volume=here:/data\n```\nThen you run the following command:\n```\ndocker run -it --rm \\\n  --volume=database_data:/data \\\n  neo4j/neo4j-admin:latest \\\n  neo4j-admin database dump neo4j --to-path=/data/\n```\n\nOnce it‚Äôs done, you start your docker container again. The dump file should be at the `/var/lib/neo4j/data/neo4j.dump`  when you connect to the container.\n\nAfter that, you can use\n```\ndocker cp <container_id_or_name>:/var/lib/neo4j/data/neo4j.dump <path_on_host>\n```\n to retrieve it.","mentions":[{"id":"720103795090260008","username":"user38128","avatar":null,"discriminator":"0","public_flags":0,"flags":0,"banner":null,"accent_color":null,"global_name":"kuser","avatar_decoration_data":null,"collectibles":null,"display_name_styles":null,"banner_color":null,"clan":null,"primary_guild":null}],"mention_roles":[],"attachments":[],"embeds":[],"timestamp":"2025-06-26T06:35:20.292000+00:00","edited_timestamp":null,"flags":0,"components":[],"id":"1387682627498283039","channel_id":"1387620561936715796","author":{"id":"1133022375051542558","username":"shabear_dis","avatar":"e5046d674427373d76e2dde9dc74feb5","discriminator":"0","public_flags":0,"flags":0,"banner":null,"accent_color":null,"global_name":"Benito","avatar_decoration_data":null,"collectibles":null,"display_name_styles":null,"banner_color":null,"clan":null,"primary_guild":null},"pinned":false,"mention_everyone":false,"tts":false,"reactions":[{"emoji":{"id":null,"name":"üëç"},"count":3,"count_details":{"burst":0,"normal":3},"burst_colors":[],"me_burst":false,"burst_me":false,"me":false,"burst_count":0}]},{"type":0,"content":"Hello team, I would like to know if the option for backup is offered in Infrahub community. What I've understood from the documentation is that this feature requires Neo4J Enterprise which is available with Infrahub Enterprise. I'd appreciate if anyone would confirm. Also is there any method of o